sentences: James Kottak (born December 26, 1962 in Louisville, Kentucky) is an American drummer.
Kottak is best known for his work with the German hard rock band Scorpions, which he joined in 1996.
At the time of his firing from the band in 2016, he was their all-time longest-serving drummer, surpassing Herman Rarebell, who spent 18 years in the band.
